This paper proposes a new mechanism called Buddy that improves the performance and efficiency of bulk bitwise operations using DRAM. The paper focuses on data-intensive applications such as bitmap indices and BitWeaving, which are commonly used in databases. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.ET (Embedded Systems).
